accessibility.text: Code coverage is a code quality metric that helps developers and QA testers measure how much coverage their test suite is covering of the codebase.
Code coverage is a code quality metric that helps developers and QA testers measure how much coverage their test suite is covering of the codebase.
It is represented in a percentage indicating the number of lines of code being run in ratio to the total number of lines of code written.
Code coverage is a code quality metric that helps developers and QA testers measure how much coverage their test suite is covering of the codebase.
It is represented in a percentage indicating the number of lines of code being run in ratio to the total number of lines of code written.
Low code coverage could be an indication of a test suite that is inclusive or code structure that is  poorly designed and hard to test.
DISCLAIMER : Having a high code coverage does not guarantee high-quality code .  A code base with high coverage can still be of poor quality/performance if the tests are not thorough.
